Introduction to Gette River

After the crossing of the Albert channel by German troops, the Belgian army has received the order to withdraw to the KW line. In order to protect that withdrawal, the "Corps de Cavalerie" (1 DC and 2 DC) has to establish a defensive line in the Gette river, between Diest and Tierlemont. According to Intelligence a sharp attack of German infantry in the locality of Halen is expected.

Your mission is to stop the Germans in the river in order to permit the redeployment of the allied armies.

Take into account that in the south, in the Small Gette, the French Cavalry Corps is engaged with the the XVI Panzerkorps and it is probable that German armoured elements will support the effort of the infantry.

